title: Foreign interference: Why France is raising its voice and turning to the courts
subhed: Since 2023, French authorities have launched nine investigations into activities such as the posting of propaganda posters, all linked to the war in Ukraine and the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. The most recent case saw three people charged, including the founder of the pro-Russian advocacy group SOS Donbass.

Gay Talese, the last titan of the American press
subhed: He was a pioneer of New Journalism, a movement that transformed American journalism with a literary writing style. At 93, the author of the landmark 1966 profile 'Frank Sinatra Has a Cold,' finds his daily life increasingly constrained by old age.

title: Paris restaurants with a New York attitude
subhed: The French capital has recently seen a wave of New York-style restaurants spring up, from slice shops to delis and red sauce joints. Parisians are flocking to these spots to savor not only a slice of culinary culture but also the enduring myth of the Big Apple.

title: How Islamology stepped out of French academia's shadows after the 2015 jihadist attacks
subhed: Once a jewel of French research, Islamology began to decline in the 1980s, but the 2015 attacks forced authorities to refocus their efforts in this field of knowledge. Although the discipline has since experienced something of a revival, its recovery remains fragile, both as an academic subject and a highly political issue.
